# himmel environment configuration.  Copy to .env (setup.sh / adopt.sh do this
# for you):  cp .env.example .env
#
# TWO kinds of variable live here, and they reach code DIFFERENTLY -- getting
# this wrong is the classic "I set it in .env but nothing happened" tax:
#
#   1. TOOL-LOADED  -- a himmel CLI reads this .env file itself, so a value here
#      is enough; no shell export needed. The Jira/Confluence CLI (scripts/jira)
#      and the Bitbucket CLI (scripts/bitbucket) load their keys straight from
#      the repo-root .env.
#
#   2. PROCESS-ENV  -- hooks, shell scripts, and skill tools read the LIVE
#      environment, NOT this file. These must be EXPORTED in the shell that
#      launches `claude`, or set in ~/.claude/settings.json "env" {} (Claude Code
#      injects that block into every session). A value sitting ONLY in this .env
#      is never seen by most of them. (Exceptions, bridged from .env by
#      scripts/lib/load-dotenv.sh: HANDOVER_DIR and USER_SLUG always; CR_PROFILE
#      + CR_CLAUDE_AGENTS by /pr-check itself (HIMMEL-558/926); and the SessionStart/SessionEnd hooks
#      read the HIMMEL_INITIATIVE* set, HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE +
#      HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE_STALE_HOURS (NOT the statusline-only _ROLLUP_TTL /
#      _SEG_TIMEOUT knobs -- those are live-env only), HIMMEL_DOC_FRESHNESS,
#      HIMMEL_WORKTREE_NUDGE and HIMMEL_JIRA_NUDGE from
#      the himmel clone's .env when they are not already exported -- HIMMEL-460.
#      Each var's own comment below says whether it is bridged.)
#
#   There is also a class of SESSION-ONLY vars (guardrail bypasses like
#   EDIT_ON_MAIN_OK, per-launch opt-ins like TELEGRAM_OWN_POLLER) that must be
#   set in the shell that LAUNCHES claude and are never read from this file --
#   inventoried in the SESSION-ONLY section near the bottom so every operator
#   flag is discoverable in one place.
#
# setup.sh / adopt.sh AUTO-SET HIMMEL_REPO for you (it is the himmel clone path,
# which the installer knows) into ~/.claude/settings.json. Run setup/adopt with
# --fill-env (PowerShell: -FillEnv) to be PROMPTED for the uncommented values
# below instead of hand-editing this file; press Enter at a prompt to skip a var
# and keep its current value. Commented (#) lines are opt-in -- uncomment first.

# === SECTION: TOOL-LOADED ===  a himmel CLI reads .env directly; no export needed

# Operator slug (HIMMEL-145). Handover bucket paths (<state-root>/<USER_SLUG>/...),
# registry.json, scratch dirs. Resolution (scripts/lib/user-slug.sh): $USER_SLUG
# -> git config user.name slugified -> fail-loud. Also bridged from .env into the
# live env by scripts/lib/load-dotenv.sh.
USER_SLUG=your-slug

# --- Jira / Confluence CLI (scripts/jira) -- reads these straight from .env ---
JIRA_BASE_URL=https://<your-site>.atlassian.net   # your Atlassian site URL
JIRA_EMAIL=<your-email@example.com>               # Atlassian account email
JIRA_API_TOKEN=your_api_token_here                # id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
# Example value -- replace with YOUR Jira project key (e.g. ACME).
JIRA_PROJECT_KEY=HIMMEL                            # default project for jira ops
JIRA_CLOUD_ID=<your-cloud-id>                      # Atlassian tenant cloud id (REST / MCP); from admin.atlassian.com or the getAccessibleAtlassianResources API
# Optional: extra projects whose metadata /jira-init caches (comma-list).
# Defaults to JIRA_PROJECT_KEY alone. himmel itself tracks HIMMEL + LUNA.
# JIRA_PROJECTS=HIMMEL,LUNA
# Optional: default Agile board id for `jira sprints` (HIMMEL-437). When set,
# `sprints` needs no --board in the common single-board case.
# JIRA_BOARD_ID=123
# Optional: custom-field id for severity (`jira edit` / CR-filed bugs). Unset ->
# `jira edit --severity` errors (the field id is required for severity edits).
# JIRA_SEVERITY_FIELD=customfield_10031
# Legacy: no active code reader as of 2026-06-20 -- kept for back-compat only.
# ORGANIZATION_ID=your_org_id_here

# --- Bitbucket Cloud CLI (scripts/bitbucket) -- only for a Bitbucket forge ---
# Reads repo-root .env or environment. Unset on a GitHub repo (never invoked).
# BITBUCKET_EMAIL=<your-email@example.com>
# BITBUCKET_API_TOKEN=your_bitbucket_api_token_here

# --- Confluence CLI (scripts/jira/dist/confluence.js) -- optional (HIMMEL-437) ---
# A scoped Jira API token 401s against Confluence (/wiki); set these to a
# Confluence-capable (scopeless/full-account) token. Unset -> the confluence CLI
# falls back to JIRA_EMAIL/JIRA_API_TOKEN.
# CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=<your-email@example.com>
# CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN=your_confluence_api_token_here

# --- Offload-lane launchers (scripts/claude-glm, scripts/claude-routed) ---
# Resolution order: LIVE process env first, else bridged from THIS .env by the
# launcher (load_dotenv). NOTE: the launcher cannot distinguish shell env from
# settings.json-injected env -- do NOT put these keys in settings.json "env"
# (that hands them to EVERY session); prefer per-launch shell env or this .env
# fallback. Set only where the lane is actually used.
# ZAI_API_KEY=your_zai_key_here             # Z.ai GLM -- claude-glm overflow lane
# OMNIROUTE_API_KEY=your_omniroute_key_here # claude-routed launcher
# Launcher tuning (LIVE env of the shell running the launcher; NOT read from
# this file):
#   GLM_MODEL / GLM_CONTEXT_WINDOW   claude-glm model + context pin (default glm-5.2 / 1M)
#   OMNIROUTE_PORT                   claude-routed local router port (default 20128)

# --- graphify extraction lane (HIMMEL-621/622) ---
# DeepSeek is the ratified extraction backend for vault corpora (egress matrix:
# luna-personal / handover-state x deepseek x extraction = allow+log). Sessions
# bridge the key from THIS .env via scripts/lib/load-dotenv.sh before launching
# `graphify --backend deepseek`; a LIVE-env export works too. (The hermes copy
# under EXTERNAL-TOOLS below is a separate consumer with its own .env.)
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your_deepseek_key_here

# === SECTION: PROCESS-ENV ===  read from the LIVE env -- EXPORT these (shell or
#     ~/.claude/settings.json "env" {}); a value ONLY in .env is NOT read, except
#     the load-dotenv-bridged vars (HANDOVER_DIR, USER_SLUG, CR_PROFILE, CR_CLAUDE_AGENTS, and the
#     HIMMEL_INITIATIVE* / HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE(+_STALE_HOURS) /
#     HIMMEL_DOC_FRESHNESS / HIMMEL_WORKTREE_NUDGE / HIMMEL_JIRA_NUDGE /
#     HIMMEL_UPDATE_AUTOSTASH set)
#     noted per-var below.

# --- himmel harness ---
# Path to your himmel checkout. The leg resolver + minerva transport anchor to it
# (marketplace/plugins/himmel-ops/scripts/legs.sh). setup.sh / adopt.sh AUTO-SET
# this into ~/.claude/settings.json; legs.sh also falls back to the default
# install path ($HOME/Documents/github/himmel). Set it explicitly only for a
# non-default clone location.  Read from the live env / settings.json (setup
# auto-sets it); NOT from this .env.
# HIMMEL_REPO=/c/path/to/your/himmel
# himmel-update autostash (HIMMEL-1197/1205). Default OFF: `node himmelctl update`
# (and the /himmel-update skill) REFUSE to pull into a dirty checkout. Set to 1 to autostash
# local changes (e.g. skill-dev diffs to skills-lock.json / .gitignore) around
# the pull and restore them after. BRIDGED from this .env by
# scripts/lib/load-dotenv.sh (HIMMEL-1205); a live shell env var still wins.
# HIMMEL_UPDATE_AUTOSTASH=1
# Statusline hud extra-cmd gate (claude-hud). AUTO-SET to 1 in settings.json by
# setup/adopt (scripts/lib/wire-statusline.sh). --extra-cmd runs arbitrary shell
# on every statusline render -- remove the settings.json entry to disable that
# surface. Live env / settings.json only; NOT read from this .env.
# CLAUDE_HUD_ALLOW_EXTRA_CMD=1
# Drive-to-ship initiative legs (HIMMEL-425/443/460). Default OFF -- opt-in, so
# keep it COMMENTED unless you want every Claude session on this MACHINE to drive
# to ship (the hook is user-scope-wired by setup/adopt and always reads THIS
# clone's .env, regardless of which directory the session was launched from).
# `1`/`all` enables the full interactive profile, or a comma-subset of:
#   plan,execute,prcheck,pr,ticket,merge,public,handover
# READ FROM .env by the SessionStart inject-initiative hook (HIMMEL-460); a value
# exported in the launching shell or set in settings.json "env" overrides it.
# Uncomment ONE line to enable (the only edit needed):
# HIMMEL_INITIATIVE=prcheck,pr,ticket,handover
# Overnight profile (HIMMEL-443): when HIMMEL_OVERNIGHT is truthy the resolver
# reads HIMMEL_INITIATIVE_OVERNIGHT instead, and `all` widens to 6 legs. Both are
# also read from .env by the hook.
# HIMMEL_OVERNIGHT=1
# HIMMEL_INITIATIVE_OVERNIGHT=all

# where-are-we ledger L2 (HIMMEL-516): opt-in SessionStart inject of the relevant
# where-are-we slice (branch-scoped ticket card, or the global digest on main).
# Default OFF (adopters see no change). Set `1` to enable; READ FROM .env by the
# SessionStart inject-where-are-we hook (ships via the himmel-ops plugin, live
# after /himmel-update + a fresh session). Same falsy grammar as HIMMEL_INITIATIVE.
# NOTE (HIMMEL-556): this same var also gates the STATUS-LINE segment, which is
# default-ON — set an explicit falsy value (0|false|off|no) to opt the status-line
# segment out. The SessionStart inject above stays opt-in (default OFF) regardless.
# HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE=1
# Staleness threshold in hours before a background ledger refresh is triggered
# (default 6). The refresh is async/detached — it never blocks session start.
# HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE_STALE_HOURS=6
# NOTE: the two status-line knobs below are LIVE-ENV ONLY (the statusline
# scripts never read .env -- unlike the two bridged flags above): export them
# or set them in settings.json "env".
# Status-line epic-rollup TTL in seconds (HIMMEL-538, default 900). The status
# line reads a CACHED jira epic rollup; when stale it fires a detached, lock-gated
# refresh — never network on the render path. Distinct from STALE_HOURS above
# (that is ledger-dock freshness in hours; this is the rollup cache interval).
# HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE_ROLLUP_TTL=900
# Status-line segment timeout in seconds (HIMMEL-538, default 5) — bounds the
# one node spawn so a hung read degrades to nothing-extra, never freezes the bar.
# HIMMEL_WHERE_ARE_WE_SEG_TIMEOUT=5

# Doc-freshness advisory (HIMMEL-587). Default OFF. "1"/"all" or a comma-subset
# of advise,session,morning. advise = /pr-check print; session = SessionStart
# nudge; morning = morning-report section. The blocking gate (doc-guard) is
# separate and always on for himmel contributors.
# HIMMEL_DOC_FRESHNESS=all

# Worktree nudge (SessionStart, opt-in, default OFF): reminds to create a
# worktree BEFORE the first blocked on-main edit. Bridged from this .env like
# HIMMEL_INITIATIVE.
# HIMMEL_WORKTREE_NUDGE=1
# Jira nudge (SessionEnd, opt-in, default OFF, advisory): "you committed
# ticket-work but never touched Jira" relay. Bridged from this .env -- and so
# are the relay credentials: the hook load_dotenv-bridges TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN +
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID from THIS .env (live env wins), so set them HERE (or export
# them) -- values only in the Telegram POLLER's own .env are NOT seen by this
# SessionEnd hook. JIRA_NUDGE_RELAY_CMD overrides the relay command entirely.
# HIMMEL_JIRA_NUDGE=1
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=            # chat id the nudge relays to (bridged from this .env)
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=          # only needed here for the nudge relay; the bridge/poller keeps its own copy

# Outbound Telegram session status (HIMMEL-1250 Increment 1, opt-in). The
# SessionEnd hook (telegram-session-end.sh) and Notification hook
# (telegram-notification.sh) relay a CONCISE status to this GROUP chat id when
# set -- unset/blank is a SILENT no-op (nothing sent). Bridged from this .env
# like TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID above; the bot token is resolved separately from the
# existing bridge/poller token file (~/.claude/channels/telegram/.env,
# TELEGRAM_ENV override) -- do NOT set TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN here for this
# feature. Never sends session content for a repo whose name matches "salus"
# (the medical vault) -- see scripts/telegram/session-status.ts.
# TELEGRAM_GROUP_CHAT_ID=

# --- Code review / pr-check critic panel (HIMMEL-558) ---
# Operator's opt-in critic profile for /pr-check. AUTHORITATIVE for the panel's
# tier filter when set (an agent can no longer scope the panel down by hand).
# Values:
#   unset    -> DEFAULT: free cross-model panel (qwen3coder anchor)
#   none     -> claude-only review; panel AND codex adversarial pass skipped
#   thorough -> tiers free,thorough
#   paid / free,paid / any comma-list -> passed through verbatim as tier filter
# READ FROM .env: /pr-check bridges it via load_dotenv (works from worktrees --
# resolves the PRIMARY checkout's .env). A live-env value (shell / settings.json
# "env") WINS over this file. Which critic sits in which tier lives in
# scripts/cr/critics.json; scorecard + drop advice: /cr-scores.
# CR_PROFILE=free,paid
# Claude reviewer agents in /pr-check (HIMMEL-926). Default OFF: the cross-model
# passes (critic panel + codex adversarial + CodeRabbit CLI) generate findings
# and the session adjudicates inline -- no pr-review-toolkit agent fan-out.
# Set to 1 to restore the per-agent dispatch matrix (pre-HIMMEL-926 behavior,
# e.g. after the CodeRabbit trial lapses). Bridged from this .env by /pr-check
# like CR_PROFILE; a live-env value wins.
# CR_CLAUDE_AGENTS=1
# Panel tuning (LIVE env only -- NOT bridged from this file):
#   CRITIC_TIMEOUT_SECS=240   per-critic wall-clock timeout (default 240, HIMMEL-558)
#   CRITIC_PARALLEL=1         run panel members concurrently (default 0 = sequential)
#   CR_USAGE_LOG=1            log estimated usage records to the critic ledger (/cr-scores)
#   CR_TRIVIALITY_OVERRIDE=full|trivial   force the triviality gate (default: heuristic)
#   CRITIC_PANEL_TIERS=free   low-level tier override, honored ONLY when CR_PROFILE unset
#   CODERABBIT_TIMEOUT_SECS=900   wall-clock cap for the CodeRabbit CLI pass (HIMMEL-926)

# --- handover + vault ---
# Handover state root (HIMMEL-335). Unset (Mode A) = inline <repo>/handovers/.
# Set (Mode B) = external dir / state repo so handover commits don't land on
# feature branches. Resolved by scripts/lib/handover-path.sh; ALSO bridged from
# this .env by scripts/lib/load-dotenv.sh when the shell didn't export it. Run
# /handover-setup to be prompted.
# HANDOVER_DIR=/c/path/to/your/handover-repo/handovers
# Handover write-flow tuning (LIVE env only -- NOT bridged from this file):
#   HANDOVER_DIRECT_MAIN=1   restore v1 commit-on-current-branch (default: branched PR flow)
#   HANDOVER_PR_AUTO=0       disable the auto PR open/update layer (default 1 = on)
#   HANDOVER_PR_BASE=main    base branch for handover PRs
#   MORNING_REPORT_LLM=1     LLM-enriched /morning-report sections (default 0 = no-token)
#   ARM_MAX_SLOTS=4          soft cap on concurrent scheduled resume slots (0 disables the cap)
# /overnight-shift ticket-selection defaults (LIVE env):
#   OVERNIGHT_PROJECT=HIMMEL   OVERNIGHT_STATUS="To Do,In Progress"
#   OVERNIGHT_LIMIT=5          OVERNIGHT_PRIORITY=key-desc
# Luna vault root for end-session-wiki capture (global default). The SessionEnd
# hook writes a note per session into <vault>/sessions/. Unset -> ~/Documents/luna.
# A per-repo .claude/end-session-wiki.json "vault_path" overrides this for that
# repo. NOT bridged -- a value in .env is ignored; EXPORT it. See
# docs/luna/end-session-wiki.md ("Choosing the target vault").
# LUNA_VAULT_PATH=/c/path/to/your/obsidian-vault
# End-session-wiki opt-out: 0/false disables the SessionEnd capture hook.
# CLAUDE_END_SESSION_WIKI=0
# Obsidian Local REST API key -- direct in-app vault delivery for
# end-session-wiki. Unset -> the hook first tries the key from the vault's own
# .obsidian/plugins/obsidian-local-rest-api/data.json, else falls back to an
# on-disk write. See /end-session-wiki-setup.
# OBSIDIAN_API_KEY=

# --- Research / AI skill keys (read from the LIVE env by the skills' tools) ---
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=     # Perplexity Sonar -- /research, /research-deep, harvest
XAI_API_KEY=            # xAI Grok -- /x-read, /x-pulse, /youtube
GEMINI_API_KEY=         # Gemini -- scripts/gemini/invoke.sh (gemini-subagent)
# SKILL_INDEX_DIR=~/.claude/skill-index   # /skill-find embedding-index location (default shown)

# --- Alibaba Qwen / DashScope (free trial available) -- provider lane ---
# One key, three endpoint flavors -- pick per consumer when the lane is wired
# (hermes provider route or a direct spawn). Key from the Alibaba Cloud Model
# Studio (bailian) console. Read from the LIVE env (export / settings.json "env").
# Verify current trial limits + endpoint URLs in the console -- Alibaba changes them.
# NOTE: the key stays inert until the Alibaba Cloud account clears real-name +
# payment verification -- calls return HTTP 403 AccessDenied.Unpurchased until then.
DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=           # Alibaba Model Studio API key
ALIBABA_OPENAI_BASE_URL=     # OpenAI-compatible endpoint (e.g. https://dashscope-intl.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1)
ALIBABA_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=  # Anthropic-compatible endpoint, if offered for your account (Claude-shaped API)
ALIBABA_DASHSCOPE_BASE_URL=  # DashScope native endpoint (e.g. https://dashscope-intl.aliyuncs.com/api/v1)

# --- VirtualBox VMs (optional) -- see docs/setup/vms.md ---
# ubuntu_vm_user=your_ubuntu_vm_username
# ubuntu_vm_pass=your_ubuntu_vm_password
# windows_vm_user=your_windows_vm_username
# windows_vm_pass=your_windows_vm_password

# === SECTION: SESSION-ONLY ===  guardrail bypasses + per-launch opt-ins. NEVER
#     read from this file -- set them in the shell that LAUNCHES claude
#     (session-sticky; a per-call `VAR=1 cmd` prefix does NOT reach PreToolUse
#     hooks). Example: `EDIT_ON_MAIN_OK=1 claude`. Inventoried here so every
#     operator flag is discoverable in one place; per-hook detail:
#     docs/internals/enforcement.md; recovery flow: docs/internals/stuck-playbook.md.
#
# Hook bypasses (PreToolUse unless noted; launching shell only):
#   EDIT_ON_MAIN_OK=1            allow Edit/Write on the primary checkout's main
#   READ_SECRETS_OK=1            allow reading secret-shaped files (.env, creds)
#   DOCKER_PRIVESC_OK=1          allow root-equivalent docker/podman mount+priv shapes
#   MERGED_PR_COMMIT_OK=1        allow committing on a branch whose PR is merged
#   ROGUE_SCHEDULE_OK=1          allow raw scheduler-arms of claude (schtasks/at/crontab)
#   MCP_ALL_OK=1                 bypass ALL backend-tier MCP routing blocks
#   MCP_<SERVICE>_OK=1           per-service bypass (e.g. MCP_JIRA_OK=1, MCP_GITHUB_OK=1)
#   GLM_EXTERNAL_WRITES_OK=1     allow external writes on the GLM lane
#   CODEX_EXTERNAL_WRITES_OK=1   same, codex adapter path
#   HERMES_EXTERNAL_WRITES_OK=1  same, hermes worker path (trusted engines only).
#                                NOT operator-set: scripts/hermes/dispatch-trusted.sh
#                                sets it internally (a hand-set inline value is
#                                classifier-denied) -- listed for inventory only
#   GRAPHIFY_SALUS_LOCAL_OK=1    allow the salus-corpus x local-ollama graphify pairing
#   GRAPHIFY_CLIPPINGS_GLM_OK=1  allow the luna-clippings x zai-glm graphify pairing
#   AUTO_ARM_DISABLE=1           kill switch: usage-cap auto-arm watchdog
#   AUTO_ARM_SUBAGENT_DISABLE=1  kill switch: subagent-cap watchdog (PostToolUse hook)
#   UPDATE_CHECK_DISABLE=1       kill switch: SessionStart "himmel behind upstream"
#                                nudge (UPDATE_CHECK_INTERVAL tunes its throttle, s)
#
# Pre-commit / pre-push gate skips (git hooks run in YOUR shell, so a per-call
# prefix DOES reach these; still last-resort -- follow the stuck-playbook first):
#   SKIP_CR=1                    skip the CR-before-push gate
#   SKIP_PR_MERGEABLE=1          skip the "open PR is CONFLICTING" pre-push gate
#   PLATFORMS_TESTED_OK=1        skip the "Platforms tested:" attestation gate
#   SKIP_SECURITY_REVIEW=1       skip the "Security reviewed:" attestation gate
#   DOC_GUARD_OK=1               skip the commands/skills doc-guard gate (himmel-dev)
#   AGENTS_MD_OK=1               skip the AGENTS.md freshness gate (himmel-dev)
#   LANES_GUARD_OK=1             skip the lanes-inventory drift guard
#   HOOKSPATH_OK=1               skip the core.hooksPath correctness check
#   SKIP_FORCE_PUSH_GATE=1       skip the no-force-push gate
#
# Script-level bypasses / per-launch opt-ins:
#   REUSE_MERGED_BRANCH_OK=1     let /worktree reuse a branch whose PR is merged
#   ARM_CHANNELS_OK=1            allow arm-resume --channels while the bun Telegram
#                                bridge is live (overrides the rc-5 refusal)
#   SKILL_TELEMETRY_DISABLE=1    kill switch for the zero-cost skill-usage telemetry
#                                (HIMMEL-236; SKILL_TELEMETRY_DIR overrides its dir)
#   GH_ADMIN_MERGE_OK=1          let pr-merge.sh retry with --admin (only when the
#                                repo has REAL branch protection -- HIMMEL-224;
#                                unnecessary --admin is classifier-vetoed)
#   TELEGRAM_OWN_POLLER=1        THIS session owns the Telegram getUpdates poll slot.
#                                Per-launch ONLY -- never export globally (one poller
#                                per token; a global export re-enables it everywhere)
#   HIMMEL_MCP_TELEGRAM=1        load the telegram plugin's outbound-only tools
#                                (reply/react) without owning the poll slot; per-launch
#   HIMMEL_MCP_LUNA_CORRELATE=1  load the luna-correlate MCP server (default-OFF
#                                mcp-gate, per-launch -- same pattern as above)

# === SECTION: EXTERNAL-TOOLS ===  key lives in the tool's OWN .env -- listed
#     here as operator inventory only; setting it in THIS file does nothing.

# --- hermes junior tier (HIMMEL-272) ---
# Live copies belong in %LOCALAPPDATA%/hermes/.env (hermes reads its own .env,
# not this file). Provider routes: NIM nemotron (default), OpenRouter,
# gemini-flash, DeepSeek, Ollama local (no key needed).
# Config-location overrides (LIVE env): HERMES_HOME (install root, default
# %LOCALAPPDATA%/hermes), HERMES_PY / HERMES_BIN (interpreter / binary override).
# NVIDIA_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# OLLAMA_API_KEY=          # Ollama Cloud only -- local ollama needs no key

# --- Telegram bridge ---
# The POLLER's TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN lives in ~/.claude/channels/telegram/.env
# (scaffolded by scripts/setup/onboard-telegram.{sh,ps1}). Operator flags read
# by the POLLER process (set where the poller runs; restart to apply):
#   TELEGRAM_AUTO_ACTIONS=arm    enable privileged auto-commands (default: all OFF;
#                                grammar mirrors HIMMEL_INITIATIVE, HIMMEL-424)
#   TELEGRAM_CLAUDE_MODEL=opus   model pin for bridge-spawned bounded runs
#                                (default opus; never inherits the operator default)
# NOTE: the HIMMEL_JIRA_NUDGE SessionEnd relay does NOT read the poller's env --
# it bridges TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN/TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID from the repo .env (see the
# jira-nudge block in PROCESS-ENV above). Session-side opt-ins
# (TELEGRAM_OWN_POLLER / HIMMEL_MCP_TELEGRAM / HIMMEL_MCP_LUNA_CORRELATE):
# SESSION-ONLY section above.
